descript.abstract: River Environment Classification (REC) is a system that classifies New Zealand's rivers according to their physical properties at a range of spatial scales. The development of REC has been supported by The Ministry for the Environment (MfE) and various regional councils to provide a spatial framework for environmental monitoring and reporting and river management.
descript.purpose: Developed by the National Institiute of Water and Atmospheric Reserch (NIWA) and Ministry for the Environment for environmental management purposes.
